President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the State of Vermont, following a severe storm that occurred from December 1-5, 2010. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas of Chittenden, Franklin, and Lamoille Counties. The funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Additionally, federal funding will be available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Albert Lewis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.